import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

# Define the base path for cloudbed-1 on March 21, 2022
base_path = "dataset/Market/cloudbed-1/telemetry/2022_03_21/"

# Read the service metric file
service_metrics = pd.read_csv(base_path + "metric/metric_service.csv")

# Convert timestamp to datetime (UTC+8)
service_metrics['datetime'] = pd.to_datetime(service_metrics['timestamp'], unit='s').dt.tz_localize('UTC').dt.tz_convert('Asia/Hong_Kong')

# Filter data between 07:30 and 08:00 on March 21, 2022
start_time = pd.Timestamp('2022-03-21 07:30:00', tz='Asia/Hong_Kong')
end_time = pd.Timestamp('2022-03-21 08:00:00', tz='Asia/Hong_Kong')
filtered_data = service_metrics[(service_metrics['datetime'] >= start_time) & (service_metrics['datetime'] <= end_time)]

# Calculate statistics for each service
stats = filtered_data.groupby('service').agg({
    'rr': ['mean', 'min', 'max', 'std'],
    'sr': ['mean', 'min', 'max', 'std'],
    'mrt': ['mean', 'min', 'max', 'std'],
    'count': ['mean', 'min', 'max', 'std']
}).reset_index()

# Flatten the multi-level columns
stats.columns = ['service', 'rr_mean', 'rr_min', 'rr_max', 'rr_std', 
                 'sr_mean', 'sr_min', 'sr_max', 'sr_std',
                 'mrt_mean', 'mrt_min', 'mrt_max', 'mrt_std',
                 'count_mean', 'count_min', 'count_max', 'count_std']

# Identify services with significant deviations
# 1. Low success rate (sr_mean < 95)
# 2. High response time (mrt_mean > 2 * global average mrt)
# 3. Low request count (count_mean < 0.5 * global average count)

global_avg_mrt = stats['mrt_mean'].mean()
global_avg_count = stats['count_mean'].mean()

deviant_services = stats[
    (stats['sr_mean'] < 95) | 
    (stats['mrt_mean'] > 2 * global_avg_mrt) | 
    (stats['count_mean'] < 0.5 * global_avg_count)
]

print("Service statistics during 07:30-08:00:")
print(stats.to_string(index=False))
print("\nServices with significant deviations:")
print(deviant_services.to_string(index=False))

import pandas as pd
import os

# Define trace file path
trace_file_path = "dataset/Market/cloudbed-1/telemetry/2022_03_21/trace/trace_span.csv"

# Check if trace file exists
if os.path.exists(trace_file_path):
    # Read trace data
    trace_df = pd.read_csv(trace_file_path)
    
    # Convert timestamp to datetime (UTC+8)
    trace_df['datetime'] = pd.to_datetime(trace_df['timestamp'], unit='ms').dt.tz_localize('UTC').dt.tz_convert('Asia/Hong_Kong')
    
    # Filter data between 07:30 and 08:00 on March 21, 2022
    start_time = pd.Timestamp('2022-03-21 07:30:00', tz='Asia/Hong_Kong')
    end_time = pd.Timestamp('2022-03-21 08:00:00', tz='Asia/Hong_Kong')
    filtered_trace = trace_df[(trace_df['datetime'] >= start_time) & (trace_df['datetime'] <= end_time)]
    
    # Identify error spans (status_code != 0)
    error_spans = filtered_trace[filtered_trace['status_code'] != 0]
    
    # Identify slow spans (duration > 1000 ms)
    slow_spans = filtered_trace[filtered_trace['duration'] > 1000]
    
    # Count errors per service
    error_counts = error_spans['cmdb_id'].value_counts().reset_index()
    error_counts.columns = ['service', 'error_count']
    
    # Count slow spans per service
    slow_counts = slow_spans['cmdb_id'].value_counts().reset_index()
    slow_counts.columns = ['service', 'slow_count']
    
    # Get top 10 longest spans
    top_longest = filtered_trace.nlargest(10, 'duration')[['datetime', 'cmdb_id', 'operation_name', 'duration', 'status_code']]
    
    # Display results
    print("Error Spans per Service:")
    print(error_counts.to_string(index=False))
    print("\nSlow Spans (>1000ms) per Service:")
    print(slow_counts.to_string(index=False))
    print("\nTop 10 Longest Spans:")
    print(top_longest.to_string(index=False))
else:
    print(f"Trace file not found: {trace_file_path}")
    
    # Check if trace directory exists
    trace_dir = "dataset/Market/cloudbed-1/telemetry/2022_03_21/trace/"
    if os.path.exists(trace_dir):
        print("\nFiles in trace directory:")
        for file in os.listdir(trace_dir):
            print(f"  - {file}")
    else:
        print(f"Trace directory not found: {trace_dir}")

# Check if log file exists

    # Read log data
    log_df = pd.read_csv(log_file_path)
    
    # Convert timestamp to datetime (UTC+8)
    log_df['datetime'] = pd.to_datetime(log_df['timestamp'], unit='s').dt.tz_localize('UTC').dt.tz_convert('Asia/Hong_Kong')
    
    # Filter data between 07:30 and 08:00 on March 21, 2022
    start_time = pd.Timestamp('2022-03-21 07:30:00', tz='Asia/Hong_Kong')
    end_time = pd.Timestamp('2022-03-21 08:00:00', tz='Asia/Hong_Kong')
    filtered_logs = log_df[(log_df['datetime'] >= start_time) & (log_df['datetime'] <= end_time)]
    
    # Define failure keywords
    failure_keywords = r'error|exception|fail|timeout|unavailable|down|crash|terminated'
    
    # Filter error logs
    error_logs = filtered_logs[filtered_logs['value'].str.contains(failure_keywords, case=False, na=False)]
    
    # Count error logs per service
    error_counts = error_logs['cmdb_id'].value_counts().reset_index()
    error_counts.columns = ['service', 'error_count']
    
    # Get top 20 frequent error messages
    error_messages = error_logs['value'].value_counts().reset_index()
    error_messages.columns = ['error_message', 'count']
    top_error_messages = error_messages.head(20)
    
    # Display results
    print("Error Logs per Service (07:30-08:00):")

    print("\nTop 20 Frequent Error Messages:")
    print(top_error_messages.to_string(index=False))

import pandas as pd
import os

# Define trace file path
trace_file_path = "dataset/Market/cloudbed-1/telemetry/2022_03_21/trace/trace_span.csv"

# Check if trace file exists
if os.path.exists(trace_file_path):
    # Read trace data
    trace_df = pd.read_csv(trace_file_path)
    
    # Convert timestamp to datetime (UTC+8)
    trace_df['datetime'] = pd.to_datetime(trace_df['timestamp'], unit='ms').dt.tz_localize('UTC').dt.tz_convert('Asia/Hong_Kong')
    
    # Filter data between 07:30 and 08:00 on March 21, 2022
    start_time = pd.Timestamp('2022-03-21 07:30:00', tz='Asia/Hong_Kong')
    end_time = pd.Timestamp('2022-03-21 08:00:00', tz='Asia/Hong_Kong')
    filtered_trace = trace_df[(trace_df['datetime'] >= start_time) & (trace_df['datetime'] <= end_time)]
    
    # Calculate total trace duration
    trace_duration = filtered_trace.groupby('trace_id').agg({
        'timestamp': ['min', 'max'],
        'status_code': lambda x: any(x != 0),
        'cmdb_id': 'first'
    }).reset_index()
    
    trace_duration['total_duration_ms'] = trace_duration['timestamp']['max'] - trace_duration['timestamp']['min']
    trace_duration['has_errors'] = trace_duration['status_code']
    trace_duration['service'] = trace_duration['cmdb_id']['first']
    
    # Filter slow and error traces
    slow_traces = trace_duration[trace_duration['total_duration_ms'] > 5000]
    error_traces = trace_duration[trace_duration['has_errors']]
    
    # Count problematic traces per service
    slow_counts = slow_traces['service'].value_counts().reset_index()
    slow_counts.columns = ['service', 'slow_trace_count']
    
    error_counts = error_traces['service'].value_counts().reset_index()
    error_counts.columns = ['service', 'error_trace_count']
    
    # Merge counts
    problematic_counts = pd.merge(slow_counts, error_counts, on='service', how='outer').fillna(0)
    
    # Get top 10 longest traces
    top_longest = trace_duration.nlargest(10, 'total_duration_ms')[['trace_id', 'service', 'total_duration_ms', 'has_errors']]
    
    # Display results
    print("Problematic Traces per Service (07:30-08:00):")
    print(problematic_counts.to_string(index=False))
    print("\nTop 10 Longest Traces:")
    print(top_longest.to_string(index=False))
else:
    print(f"Trace file not found: {trace_file_path}")
